e to violent crime, especially in areas like \"Over the Hill.\" Vacation rentals may lack security.Swimming & Watercraft Hazards: Risks include unlicensed jet ski operators, sexual assaults, and boating accidents. Travelers should avoid swimming alone and stay alert near watercraft.Firearms & Ammunition Restrictions: Firearms and ammunition are illegal. U.S. citizens have been detained for inadvertently carrying them.Safety Tips: Stay aware of surroundings, secure accommodations, and sign up for the Smart Traveler Enrollment Program (STEP) for real-time updates.Do you have a REAL ID?Are you travel‐ready? Starting May 7, 2025, to board domestic flights your driver's license or state issued ID must be a REAL ID or you'll need another acceptable form of identification, such as a passport.If you haven't already, now is the time to visit your state's DMV and get your REAL IDMore details: Real ID and more new travel requirements: What you need to know. Youtube  Iceland Volcano UpdateVolcanic Activity: Iceland's Reykjanes Peninsula has experienced its 11th eruption since 2021. The April 1 eruption caused evacuations in Grindavik and the Blue Lagoon, although it hasn't disrupted major travel routes or Reykjavik.Travel Impact: The eruption has not affected flights or the capital city, but tourists should monitor local news for updates. The Blue Lagoon remains closed until April 2 as a precaution.Safety Advice: The FCDO advises staying informed of ongoing volcanic activity, which may continue for decades. Travelers should follow local authorities’ advice and be aware of risks like landslides and volcanic gases. INSIDER TRAVEL HACKBook window and aisle seats to keep the middle open","category":"Newsletter Ads","description":"","author":"The Blink","date":"2025-04-04","hasAds":true,"url":"https://theblinkdaily.beehiiv.com/p/your-face-might-just-replace-your-boarding-pass-b67a5b121836f2ee","publisher":{"name":"The Blink","url":"https://theblinkdaily.beehiiv.com"},"advertisers":[